            <div type="note" subtype="biographical">
                <head type="title"><persName corresp="#AW">Alexander D. O. (Dundas Ogilvy) Wedderburn</persName> (<date notBefore="1854" notAfter="1931">1854&#x2013;1931</date>)</head>
                <p><persName corresp="#JR">Ruskin</persName>&#x02BC;s secretary, 18??&#x2013;<!--Entry needed here-->??; barrister, from <!--Entry needed here-->???; King&#x02BC;s
                    Counsel, from ????<!-- Entry needed here --> </p>
                <p><persName corresp="#THILTON">Hilton</persName> points out that <persName corresp="#AW">Wedderburn</persName> stood apart from his fellow <orgName corresp="#OXFORDU">Balliol College</orgName>
                    followers of <persName corresp="#JR">Ruskin</persName>, Arnold Toynbee and Alfred Milner, ...<!-- Entry needed here --></p>
                <p>After <persName corresp="#JR">Ruskin</persName>&#x02BC;s death, by terms of the will, <persName corresp="#AW">Wedderburn</persName> was named literary trustee
                    along with <persName corresp="#CEN">Charles Eliot Norton</persName> and <persName corresp="#JSAR">Joan Severn</persName>. He also received a third of the
                    profits from books (subsequently?<!-- Entry needed here -->) edited or revised by him, along with &#x00A3;100 a
                    year to supervise sales. In <date when="1900">1900</date>, on <persName corresp="#JR">Ruskin</persName>&#x02BC;s death, <persName corresp="#AW">Wedderburn</persName> advised Allen
                    and the trustees that, to maintain copyright, they should issue new editions of
                    <persName corresp="#JR">Ruskin</persName>&#x02BC;s works incorporating formerly unpublished material. </p>
                <p><persName corresp="#AW">Wedderburn</persName> appears to have been responsible for arranging and binding
                    <persName corresp="#JR">Ruskin</persName>&#x02BC;s manuscripts after <date when="1900">1900</date>, once work began on the <title type="book" corresp="#JRWORKSLE"><hi rend="italic">Library
                    Edition</hi></title>, and he prepared the catalog of manuscripts for the bibliography volume
                    (vol. 38). </p>
                <p><ref type="bibliography" target="bibliography.php#DEARDENLIBRARYEDITION"><persName corresp="#JSD">Dearden</persName>, <title type="essay" corresp="DEARDENLIBRARYEDITION">&#x201C;Library Edition of the Works of John Ruskin,&#x201D;</title></ref>
                    52&#x2013;53, 61; </p>
            </div>
